          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "KINDT"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 4He gas was contained in a cylindrical cell of",
                " diameter 7.6 cm and height 6.2 cm with 0.03 mm thick",
                " metal walls. With the beam on the target the gas",
                " temperature was about 34 K and the pressure was",
                " 0.66 mpA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "REC",
                "MAGFR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Detecting of the recoiling A = 3 nuclei",
                " using 900 MeV/C magnetic spectrometer."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MWDC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two multiwire gas proportional counters were",
                " used. The thickness of each counter was 14.7 mg/cm2.",
                " The active area of each counter was 76 x 36 cm, they",
                " had uniform gain over the central 66 x 20 cm region."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The measured particle momentum spectra were converted",
                " to photodisintegration cross sections as a function",
                " of real or virtual photon energy by dividing by the",
                " appropriate Jacobians and the corresponding",
                " calculated photon spectrum."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The measured particle yields were corrected for",
                "  events lost due to the rate limitation of the data",
                "  acquisitions ystem and for the drift chamber",
                "  inefficiency."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-SYS",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Systematic uncertainty is about 9%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Measurement of the differential cross sections for the",
                " 4He(gamma,n)3He and 4He(gamma,p)3H reactions have",
                " been performed for photon energies in the 100 - 360",
                " MeV region. Results were obtained for nucleon",
                " center-of-mass angles close to 60, 90, and 120 degree",
                " by detecting the recoiling nuclei with a magnetic",
                " spectrometer. Both (gamma,p) and (gamma,n) cross",
                " sections are forward peaked and fall rapidly as a",
                " function of photon energy. The (gamma,p) to (gamma,n)",
                " cross section ratio is in the range 0.7 - 1.3 at each",
                " angle and tends to increase with photon energy. The",
                " data were compared with a calculation by Gari and",
                " Hebach which includes meson exchange contributions.",
                " The magnitude and energy dependence of the cross",
                " sections are approximately reproduced, but the theory",
                " fails to describe the angular dependence and the",
                " cross section ratios."
              ]
            }
          ],
